The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Wife killed for denying sex
                                                                                                               Wife killed for denying sex
                            
	Chennai, April 4 (PTI): A man allegedly killed his wife after she refused to have sex with him and later had intercourse with the corpse, police said today.        
	Subash allegedly strangled his wife with a skipping rope after she spurned him for his failure to earn a steady income.         
	The incident came to light when the children found their mothers body and informed the relatives.        
	Subash was later arrested, police said. The couple had been married for 10 years and quarrelled frequently.                                                                                                                                                                           
